D=1515.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   A few questions about damage spells</span><hr size=1>     There are several spells magicians have to choose from that do damage, some are magic based, some fire based.  My question is basically, if I want to maximize my damage per second in a group, using some form of damage spell, which spell is &quot;the one?&quot;  Which spell is the best DPS magic based spell?  Which one is the best DPS fire based spell?  Mana ratios are not to be considered for this particular argument.  Also, counting any crits from SCF, which spells are the best DPS magic/fire spells?  Does anyone have a rundown? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uailees.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ailees</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/maitres/ailees.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 623<br> <font color=#333333>(9/6/02 9:34:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1515.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/citation/ailee-ep2.jpg width=130 height=164></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A few questions about damage spells</span><hr size=1> what do you call &quot;best&quot; if mana ratio does not count ?<br>
